Project Name: Website Scanning Using Nmap
Designation: Network Engineer
Software Used: Nmap.
Required OS: Kali Linux.

Project Description:
The project focuses on scanning and examining a website on the target and identifying its vulnerabilities and potential security weaknesses utilizing the Network Mapper tool implemented in the kali Linux OS. At first, I was engaged as a Network Engineer and obtained permission from the client for scanning, testing, and various other tasks. Obtaining permission from the client is essential.


My Roles and Responsibilities:
•	Optimized security policies to confirm to industry best practices and client-specific business demands.
•	Conducted network scanning using Nmap to discover all open ports and services.
•	Executed comprehensive Nmap scanning techniques across all 65,535 ports to identify open ports, running services, version detection, and OS detection, effectively mapping the website's attack surface.
•	Interpreted scan results to pinpoint high-risk areas and potential security weaknesses.
•	Prepared detailed scan reports, including identified risks, and mitigation strategies.
•	Maintained documentation for technical reference and future audits. 
•	Collaborated with the project manager to review findings and validate issues.
•	Compiled comprehensive vulnerability assessment reports, detailing risk levels, technical findings, and actionable recommendations to strengthen the overall security posture.
•	Recommended patching, port filtering, and service hardening based on scan results.
